The paper describes a planning methodology for domains with uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methodology involves backward chaining and analyzing the probability of success of the partial plan, which are topics in planning (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions using Monte Carlo simulation and Markov chain representation, which are techniques commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
